    synthetic_data.append([current_material, current_thickness, pulse_width, energy, intensity, power, cutoff_energy])

    synthetic_data.append([current_material, current_thickness, pulse_width, energy, intensity, power, cutoff_energy])
    
# Now we've got to the 25th point, but remember that generating exactly 25 with unique samples requires ensuring uniqueness or adjusting ranges/distributions accordingly. We will just demonstrate this last part for now.
